left click wifi symbol, navigate to advanced options, edit connections

double click ethernet

ipv4 settings

change method to manual

add address (need to be non-routable ip address....can google some)
NOTE: set the raspberry pi Static IP to a class B address because windows will default to class B addresses when connecting different ethernets... so it will auto work with the pi without needing to change anything.

    - THIS IS RECOMMENDED 169.254.something.something (subnet) (this has the least amount to do for user)  

  

    

EXAMPLE
    ip address 169.254.50.42
    netmask 255.255.0.0 (default for class b address)
    gateway no need

    TEST by running ifconfig on rpi. on windows use ipconfig and you should see the new ip address on ethernet

	can now connect to the new ip address on vnc
